WEBVTT

00:01.510 --> 00:03.777
So here we go.
What letter are we up to now?

00:03.812 --> 00:04.778
J's. My crown is my crown.

00:04.814 --> 00:07.814
So, jeremiah if it's a boy,

00:07.850 --> 00:09.550
Or jacinta if it's a girl.

00:09.585 --> 00:12.553
Jeremiah sexton-jenkins.

00:12.588 --> 00:14.922
I like it. My god, it's a boy?

00:14.957 --> 00:18.392
Or jacinta sexton-jenkins.

00:18.427 --> 00:20.060
You're having fun torturing me.

00:20.096 --> 00:22.141
By not telling me the gender
of the baby, aren't you?

00:22.165 --> 00:23.030
A little, but hey,

00:23.065 --> 00:26.433
If I can wait 21 more weeks,
so can you.

00:28.838 --> 00:31.005
Dr. Rhodes?

00:31.040 --> 00:32.640
Page me if you need me.

00:32.674 --> 00:33.807
Case coming your way.

00:33.843 --> 00:35.743
Window washer fell 33 stories.

00:35.778 --> 00:38.412
Should be doa,
but still alive... Barely.

00:38.447 --> 00:40.814
33? Press will be all over this.

00:40.850 --> 00:42.816
Hospital pr's gonna be involved.

00:42.852 --> 00:45.486
Get ready for your close-up.

00:48.491 --> 00:50.090
Okay, who's next?

00:50.126 --> 00:51.525
Damian butler.

00:51.561 --> 00:54.862
Damian butler? That's me.

00:54.897 --> 00:55.996
God.

00:56.032 --> 00:57.665
Won't be much longer.

00:57.700 --> 00:58.933
It's just I have the flu.

00:58.968 --> 01:01.569
It's low priority. I get it.

01:02.738 --> 01:03.704
Sir?

01:03.739 --> 01:05.873
Maggie, how many minutes out?
They're here.

01:05.908 --> 01:08.209
Baghdad's prepped. Thanks.

01:11.013 --> 01:14.481
Justin pepper, 23,
long fall, axial load injury.

01:14.517 --> 01:16.450
After his window washing
platform gave out.

01:16.485 --> 01:19.787
Gcs, 3... bp, 70 over palp...
Heart rate, 135.

01:19.822 --> 01:20.899
All right, that long a fall,
we're looking at.

01:20.923 --> 01:23.691
Injuries to the brain, spine,
chest, and abdomen,

01:23.726 --> 01:25.226
Let alone long bone fractures.

01:25.261 --> 01:27.661
Maggie, I need extra hands
and an o.R. On alert.

01:27.697 --> 01:28.796
Done.

01:28.831 --> 01:31.532
What's he got for iv access?
16 gauge on both arms.

01:31.567 --> 01:33.033
All right,
very gently, everybody.

01:33.069 --> 01:36.870
On my count, one, two, three.

01:38.007 --> 01:40.074
Good luck. Thanks.

01:40.109 --> 01:41.809
All right,
likely cavitary bleeding.

01:41.844 --> 01:44.511
Wheeler, get a groin line.
Start the mtp.

01:44.547 --> 01:47.047
Hang two units of o-neg
on the rapid transfuser.

01:47.083 --> 01:48.983
Until we type and cross.
X-rays...

01:49.018 --> 01:51.218
I need chest, pelvis,
and c-spine.

01:51.254 --> 01:52.731
And let's get
the ultrasound over here.

01:52.755 --> 01:53.821
To fast his belly.

01:53.856 --> 01:54.622
Lungs are clear. All right.

01:54.657 --> 01:55.867
I'm gonna start the groin line.

01:55.891 --> 01:57.258
Help me reduce
this leg fracture.

01:57.293 --> 02:00.194
Come on, come on.
One, two, three...

02:01.731 --> 02:03.697
X-ray. All right, step back.

02:09.572 --> 02:11.171
Pelvis down.

02:11.207 --> 02:13.007
C-spine. On the box.

02:15.711 --> 02:17.945
Chest x-ray is up.
Tension hemopneumothorax.

02:17.980 --> 02:20.047
Trachea shifted,
venous return is down.

02:20.082 --> 02:21.248
Give me a chest tube.

02:21.284 --> 02:22.516
Show me the pelvis.

02:22.551 --> 02:23.484
Got it.

02:23.519 --> 02:25.686
Vertical shear of
the left hemipelvis...

02:25.721 --> 02:27.187
It needs traction.

02:27.223 --> 02:28.856
Pull up the c-spine.

02:28.891 --> 02:29.923
Up.

02:29.959 --> 02:33.794
Multiple c-spine fractures.

02:33.829 --> 02:36.230
Wheeler, how's that groin line?
Done.

02:36.265 --> 02:37.698
All right, chest tube's in too.

02:37.733 --> 02:38.599
Let's move.

02:38.634 --> 02:41.035
Justin didn't survive
a 330-foot fall.

02:41.070 --> 02:42.703
Just to die in my trauma bay.

02:42.738 --> 02:44.104
Let's go, let's go! Go.

